Hi,<br />win 7 64 bit pro <br />Classic Shell (installed month ago)<br />drives mentioned are all internal.<br /><br />I maximise explorer, select E drive, open a folder at left pane, examine contents visually then click on E drive again and all is well, explorer windows stays maximised, open  another folder then minimise window.<br />Open a new instance of windows explorer and again select E drive to examine a different folder, open the folder, then click on E drive and the window loses maximisation, its part off and on screen lower right.<br /><br /><br /><strong>If I have two or more instances of win explorer open for E drive, the second and subsequent ones won't hold maximisation.</strong><br /><br />Try again this time first window E drive, then create another for D and both behave ok and hold maximisation.<br /><br />Try another experiment, both this time D drive and both behave.<br /><br />I am unable to have two windows open for E drive, without forever having to maximise the window after every move backwards in the address !<br /><br />If I have the windows both for D then navigate to E they behave !<br /><br />Another test, close all explorers that are open, then open explorer , it opens maximised. and click J drive then minimise, open another explorer and click J drive, still ok, still maximised. so I have two for J both stay maximised.<br />carry on for the other drives, all stay maximised for the second matching drive letter,<br />D though this time loses maximisation,   E lives up to its reputation as always.<br /><br />Trouble is I am using E drive a lot so this is a real pain.<br /><br />DBenz<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4672">DBenz</a> — Sat Dec 13, 2014 7:07 am</p><hr />
